{"id":22531,"category_id":1,"owner":"BBC","created_at":"29/11/2011","title":"زيادة عمليات التسوق عبر الإنترنت","pictures":"//wscdn.bbc.co.uk/worldservice/assets/images/2011/11/29/111129121106_le_xtra_shopping_624x351_pa.jpg","active":1,"views":87,"content":"Online shopping is on the rise; yesterday marked the biggest day for internet sales in the UK and the US. \r\nEven though the current state of the economy means people are spending less, this is the busiest time of year for shopping. The day after Thanksgiving in the US – last Friday – usually marks the beginning of the Christmas shopping season. It's known as 'Black Friday' and there are lots of discounts on that day. \r\nChristmas shopping can be a miserable experience because of the crowds; it's how Black Friday got its name. So now a lot of us are buying items over the internet rather than going out to the shops. \r\nIt's predicted that 25% of all Christmas shopping this year will be done over the internet, up 16 % on last year.\r\nThere are a number of reasons for this. Often buying online not only means you don't have to go out and fight the crowds and the weather but you can also shop around a lot easier and get better bargains. \r\nIt's also becoming much easier to shop online. More people are using their smart devices such as phones and tablets to access the internet and we are becoming more accustomed to using the internet for shopping. Retailers have caught on to this and many more have online shopping sites. \r\nWhat do you think? What are the main advantages of shopping online or in the shops? Where's the best place to pick up a bargain?\r\nWrite to us in English!Rise of online shopping\r\nListen to the words\r\nاستمعmp3.لاستخدام هذا الملف لابد من تشغيل برنامج النصوص \"جافا\"، وأحدث الإصدارات من برنامج \"فلاش بلاير\"\r\nأحدث إصدارات برنامج \"فلاش بلاير\" متاحة هنااعرض الملف في مشغل آخر\r\nonline shopping\r\nالتسوق من خلل الإنترنت \r\nThanksgiving\r\nعيد الشكر \r\nthe Christmas shopping season\r\nموسم